      "anchor_concept_id": "spine_psychology_neuroscience_l3_personality_disorders_overview",
      "content": {
        "title": "DSM Personality Disorder Clusters",
        "definition": "DSM groups personality disorders into Cluster A (odd/eccentric), Cluster B (dramatic/erratic), and Cluster C (anxious/fearful), organizing overlapping symptom patterns for clinical and educational framing.",
        "summary": "Cluster A includes paranoid, schizoid, and schizotypal; Cluster B includes antisocial, borderline, histrionic, and narcissistic; Cluster C includes avoidant, dependent, and obsessive-compulsive personality disorders."
      },
